The paper proposes a deep learning model for time series forecasting, specifically addressing the challenges of capturing long-term patterns and incorporating information from other variables while maintaining interpretability. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they are the most general and encompass a wide range of deep learning research. The other categories are also possible as they are related to specific aspects of the proposed model, such as the attention mechanism (cs.SI) and the potential application to image data (cs.CV).
